# 🐞 bug report

### Affected Package
@angular/core


### Is this a regression?
No, it's a schematic for 11 migration


### Description
As I understand correctly, the added migration in this PR: https://github.com/angular/angular/pull/39212 should replace async with waitForAsync. I have a ton of spec files lined up like this:

```
import { async, TestBed } from '@angular/core/testing';
describe('@myApp, () => {
  describe('AppComponent', () => {
    beforeEach(async(() => {
      TestBed.configureTestingModule({
        imports: [TestHostModule],
      }).compileComponents();
    }));

```
I do get the deprecation warning for the use of async. But the schematic is not taking effect.

I have tried to figure out why it is not happening. The file seems to be loaded by the schematic, but it never validates this:

```
      if (!asyncImportSpecifier || !asyncImport) {
        return;
      }

```

as being false. The typescript helper function 'getImportSpecifier' simply always returns false on: "node.moduleSpecifier.text === moduleName"


